    <etym xml:lang="ru">К основе %istū-%i, %istav-%i (вариант общераспространенного индоевропейского
        корня %istā-%i: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II 607
                сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II 607 ff.</biblScope></bibl>) ‘стоять’,
        ‘ставить’, с наращением префикса <ref type="xr" target="#entry_o-"/>. Аналогичное развитие
        значения основы %istā-%i, %istav-%i в сторону анатомических понятий мы находим в славянских:
            <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
            ><lang/><w>стан</w><gloss><q>фигура</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>талия</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><w>остов</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из %iостав%i)</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from
            %iостав%i)</note><gloss><q>скелет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><w>сустав</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                    ><lang/><w>става</w><gloss><q>сустав</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="bg"><lang/><w>став</w><gloss><q>тело</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="bg"><w/><gloss><q>сустав</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="bg"
                ><w>става</w><gloss><q>член тела</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Miklosich"/><biblScope>319</biblScope></bibl>); ср. также <mentioned
            xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>astū́</w><gloss><q>шея</q></gloss></mentioned>, при <mentioned
            xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>ustu(n)-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>sūtūn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
            ><lang/><w>ʼstʼwn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
            ><lang/><w>stuna-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>sthū́ṇā-</w><gloss><q>столб</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>колонна</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ZDMG"/><biblScope>XXXVII49, 48</biblScope></bibl>). См. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_styn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_stajyn"/>, сюда же, очевидно, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_staw"/> | %istawær%i ‘поясничная область’ (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Сл."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр.
                1123</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p. 1123</biblScope></bibl> — под вопросом,
        нам не встречалось).</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">To the stem %istū-%i, %istav-%i (variant of the common Indo-European root
        %istā-%i: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II 607
                сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II 607 ff.</biblScope></bibl>) ‘stand’,
        ‘put’, with augment of the prefix <ref type="xr" target="#entry_o-"/>. A similar development
        of the meaning of the stem%istā-%i, %istav-%i towards anatomical concepts can be found in
        Slavic languages: <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
            ><lang/><w>стан</w><gloss><q>figure</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>waist</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><w>остов</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из %iостав%i)</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from
